citeinfo.title: Township map of Fujian with 2000 Census short form data

descript.abstract: Township locations in Fujian Province, China, with 2000 Census data from short form tables A1-A8 (100% counts). Includes general information, age composition, households, deaths, household registration, and housing.
descript.supplinf: "The data is updated by end of 2000 year"

overview.eaover: Data Categories are as follows. A) General Information of the 2000 population Census data: 1-1, Family households, population and sex ratio by township. 1-2, Population by sex, household registration status. 1-3, Status of registered population by sex and township. 1-4, In–coming population from different household registration places by sex and township. 1-5, Agricultural and non-agricultural population by sex and township. 1-6, Population by sex, nationality and by township. 1-7, Population by sex, age and by township. 1-8, Population aged 6 and over by sex, education attainment and township. 1-9, Illiterate population aged 15 and over by sex and township. 1-10, Family households by size and township. 1-11, Family households by type and township. 1-12, Births by sex , month of birth and by township (1999.11.1-2000.10.31). 1-13, Deaths by sex, month of death and by township ( 1999.11.1-2000.10.31). 1-14, Number of rooms and space of family households by township. B) Age composition Information of the 2000 population Census data: 3-2, Index of age composition by Township (I). 3-3, Index of age composition by Township (II). C) Household Information of the 2000 population Census data: 5-1, Family households by size and type. 5-2, Family households with only one member by age and sex and by Township. 5-3, Family households with one or more than one nationalities by Township. 5-4, Family households with persons aged 0-19 by Township. 5-5, Family households with persons aged 60 and over by Township. 5-6, Family households with persons aged 65 and over by Township. D) Death Information of the 2000 population Census data: 6-1, Deaths by sex, age and Township (1999.11.1-2000.10.31). 6-2, Deaths aged 6 and over by sex, education attainment and by Township (1999.11.1-2000.10.31). 6-3, Deaths aged 15 and over by sex, marital status and by Township (1999.11.1-2000.10.31). E) Household registration Information of the 2000 population Census data: 7-1, Population by current residence and place of household registration. 7-2, Population by current residence and place of household registration in other regions. F) Housing Information of the 2000 population Census data: 8-1, Family households by number of dwelling rooms and by Township. 8-2, Family households by dwelling space per person and by Township. 8-3, Family households by number of generations, dwelling rooms and by Township.

offoptn.compat: List of the 5th China Population Census Data Product Series. 1) The Completed Collection of China County/District Population Census Data Assemblies: The Collection includes more than 2,876 electronic books with more than 330,000 tables for all China 2000 county/district population census data assemblies, which provide extensive coverage at county, urban district and township levels. The data include rich information on general population, nationalities, marriage, age, education, occupation, housing, migration, etc. For more information, please visit: http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/census2000cnty.htm 2) The Completed Collection of National and Provincial Population Census Data Assemblies: The "Collection" includes all 32 China 2000 population census data assemblies with about 14,200 tables, which provide extensive coverage at national, provincial, city and county levels (see the list of all book in the attachment). All data tables are available in Excel files on the CD product. The users can use any web browser to browse the data by province. All table titles of the "Collection" are in both Chinese and English. For more information, please visit: http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/census2000prov.htm 3) The Township GIS maps with 2000 Population Census Data: The GIS maps include locations of townships (Xiang, Zhen and Jiedao), counties, prefectures, and provincial capitals, the county boundaries, the provincial boundaries, roads, rivers, and lakes. An online demo is available at http://gis.umdl.umich.edu/website/beijing/viewer.htm 4) The 2000 County Population Census Data with County Maps: The 2000 county data include 2000 county boundary GIS map and includes several other GIS maps. There are about 201 attribute variables integrated with the county map, including 170 population variables from 2000 census for counties and urban cities and 31 socioeconomic variables for each county. See details at http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/BookListDetail.asp?ID=1011 5) 2000 China Province Population Census Data with Provincial Map: The data include 2000 provincial GIS maps with more than 5000 attribute variables. See more details at http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/BookListDetail.asp?ID=1012 6) China City Statistical Indicators with Maps (1996-2001): This CD product includes a series of city statistical indicators with GIS maps from 1996 to 2001 with more than 200 variables. See more details at http://chinadatacenter.org/newcdc/BookListDetail.asp?ID=1255
